messages.content:
 Now I understand the issue! The problem is at lines 5670-5672:

```cpp
auto CmpXZ = IsCondKnownTrue(simplifyICmpInst(Pred, X, Z, Q));
auto CmpYZ = IsCondKnownTrue(simplifyICmpInst(Pred, Y, Z, Q));
if (!CmpXZ.has_value() && !CmpYZ.has_value())
  return nullptr;
```

This early return happens BEFORE the clamp pattern check (lines 5691-5732). When we have the pattern `icmp eq Z, smin(smax(Z, LoC), HiC)`, neither simplification of X or Y against Z will succeed with a known result, so the function returns early without ever checking the clamp pattern.

The fix is to move the clamp pattern matching BEFORE the early return, or modify the early return condition.

Let me apply the fix:

